title: Walt Whitman to William Michael Rossetti, 23 March [1876]
text: Camden, N. Jersey—U. S. America—March 23Yours of March 5 recd.received with enc.enclosed—Books will be sent hence by Baldwin's Express (office in London, H. Starr & Co. 22 Moorgate st)—will probably arrive there somewhere ab'tabout 10th or 12th April. I sent a set (L of GLeaves of Grass and Two Riv.Rivulets Two Vols.Volumes in one package) to you by mail March 15—& another set two Vols.Volumes same date, to Mrs. G[ilchrist]—but have since learn'dlearned that such packages are overweight, & fear they may not have been forwarded from N. Y. I wrote you letter March 17—I sent a single Vol.Volume (Two RivRivulets) by mail, March 20—I continue about the same.W.W. Walt Whitman to William Michael Rossetti, 23 March [1876]
